<a name="Description" id="Description"></a><h2> <span class="mw-headline"> Description </span></h2>
<p>Used on single post <a href="/Glossary#Permalink" title="Glossary">permalink</a> pages, this template tag displays a link to the next post which exists in chronological order from the current post.
</p><p>This tag must be used in <a href="/The_Loop" title="The Loop">The Loop</a>.
</p>
<a name="Usage" id="Usage"></a><h2> <span class="mw-headline"> Usage </span></h2>
<pre>&lt;?php next_post_link('format', 'link', 'in_same_cat', 'excluded_categories');&nbsp;?&gt;</pre>
<a name="Parameters" id="Parameters"></a><h2> <span class="mw-headline"> Parameters </span></h2>
<dl><dt> <tt>format</tt>
</dt><dd> (<a href="/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String" title="How to Pass Tag Parameters"><i>string</i></a>) (<i>Optional</i>) Format string for the link. This is where to control what comes before and after the link. <tt>'%link'</tt> in string will be replaced with whatever is declared as <tt>'link'</tt> (see next parameter). <tt>'Go to&nbsp;%link'</tt> will generate "Go to &lt;a href&#61;..." Put HTML tags here to style the final results.
<dl><dd> Default: <tt>'%link &amp;raquo;'</tt> 
</dd></dl>
</dd></dl>
<dl><dt> <tt>link</tt>
</dt><dd> (<a href="/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String" title="How to Pass Tag Parameters"><i>string</i></a>) (<i>Optional</i>) Link text to display.
<dl><dd> Default: <tt>'%title'</tt> (next post's title) 
</dd></dl>
</dd></dl>
<dl><dt> <tt>in_same_cat</tt>
</dt><dd> (<a href="/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Boolean" title="How to Pass Tag Parameters"><i>boolean</i></a>) (<i>optional</i>) Indicates whether next post must be within the same category as the current post. If set to <tt>'true'</tt>, only posts from the current category will be displayed. If the post is in both the parent and subcategory, or more than one category, the next post link will lead to the next post in any of those categories.
<ul><li> <tt>1</tt> (true)
</li><li> <tt>0</tt> (false)(default)
</li></ul>
<dl><dd> Default: false
</dd></dl>
</dd></dl>
<dl><dt> <tt>excluded_categories</tt>
</dt><dd> (<a href="/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String.2Farray" title="How to Pass Tag Parameters"><i>string/array</i></a>) (<i>optional</i>) Array or a comma-separated list of numeric category IDs from which the next post should not be listed. <b>Note</b>: Previous versions of WordPress used to have IDs separated by " and ". Example: <tt>'1 and 5 and 15'</tt>
<dl><dd> Default: <i>None</i>
</dd></dl>
</dd></dl>
<a name="Examples" id="Examples"></a><h2> <span class="mw-headline"> Examples  </span></h2>
<a name="Default_Usage" id="Default_Usage"></a><h3> <span class="mw-headline">Default Usage</span></h3>
<p>Displays link with the post title of the next post (chronological post date order), followed by a right angular quote (&raquo;).
</p>
<div style="border:1px solid blue; width:50%; padding:10px"><a href="#Examples" title="">Next Post Title &raquo;</a></div>
<p><code><span style="color: #000000">
&nbsp;<span style="color: #0000BB">&lt;?php&nbsp;next_post_link</span><span style="color: #007700">();&nbsp;</span><span style="color: #0000BB">?&gt;</span>&nbsp;</span>
</code>
</p>
<a name="Bold_Post_Title_As_Link" id="Bold_Post_Title_As_Link"></a><h3> <span class="mw-headline">Bold Post Title As Link</span></h3>
<p>Displays link with next chronological post's title wrapped in 'strong' tags (typically sets text to bold).
</p>
<div style="border:1px solid blue; width:50%; padding:10px"><a href="#Examples" title=""><strong>Next Post Title</strong></a></div>
<p><code><span style="color: #000000">
&nbsp;<span style="color: #0000BB">&lt;?php&nbsp;next_post_link</span><span style="color: #007700">(</span><span style="color: #DD0000">'&lt;strong&gt;%link&lt;/strong&gt;'</span><span style="color: #007700">);&nbsp;</span><span style="color: #0000BB">?&gt;</span>&nbsp;</span>
</code>
</p>
<a name="Text_As_Link.2C_Without_Post_Title.2C_Within_Same_Category" id="Text_As_Link.2C_Without_Post_Title.2C_Within_Same_Category"></a><h3> <span class="mw-headline">Text As Link, Without Post Title, Within Same Category</span></h3>
<p>Displays custom text as link to the next post within the same category as the current post. Post title is not included here. "Next post in category" is the custom text, which can be changed to fit your requirements.
</p>
<div style="border:1px solid blue; width:50%; padding:10px"><a href="#Examples" title="">Next post in category</a></div>
<p><code><span style="color: #000000">
&nbsp;<span style="color: #0000BB">&lt;?php&nbsp;next_post_link</span><span style="color: #007700">(</span><span style="color: #DD0000">'%link'</span><span style="color: #007700">,&nbsp;</span><span style="color: #DD0000">'Next&nbsp;post&nbsp;in&nbsp;category'</span><span style="color: #007700">,&nbsp;</span><span style="color: #0000BB">TRUE</span><span style="color: #007700">);&nbsp;</span><span style="color: #0000BB">?&gt;</span>&nbsp;</span>
</code>
</p>
<a name="Within_Same_Category.2C_Excluding_One" id="Within_Same_Category.2C_Excluding_One"></a><h3> <span class="mw-headline">Within Same Category, Excluding One</span></h3>
<p>Displays link to next post in the same category, as long as it is not in category 13 (the category ID #). You can change the number to any category you wish to exclude. Exclude multiple categories by using "<tt> and </tt>" as a delimiter.
</p>
<div style="border:1px solid blue; width:50%; padding:10px"><a href="#Examples" title="">Next post in category</a></div>
<p><code><span style="color: #000000">
&nbsp;<span style="color: #0000BB">&lt;?php&nbsp;next_post_link</span><span style="color: #007700">(</span><span style="color: #DD0000">'%link'</span><span style="color: #007700">,&nbsp;</span><span style="color: #DD0000">'Next&nbsp;post&nbsp;in&nbsp;category'</span><span style="color: #007700">,&nbsp;</span><span style="color: #0000BB">TRUE</span><span style="color: #007700">,&nbsp;</span><span style="color: #DD0000">'13'</span><span style="color: #007700">);&nbsp;</span><span style="color: #0000BB">?&gt;</span>&nbsp;</span>
</code>
</p>
<a name="Notes" id="Notes"></a><h2> <span class="mw-headline"> Notes </span></h2>
<p>See also <a href="/Template_Tags/previous_post_link" title="Template Tags/previous post link" class="mw-redirect">previous_post_link()</a>.
</p>
